messages.content:
Analyze this build manifest and extract build system information. Respond with JSON ONLY.

Manifest: universalbuild.json
Content:
[
  {
    "build": {
      "cache": [
        ".m2/repository",
        "target"
      ],
      "commands": [
        "mvn package -DskipTests"
      ],
      "env": {
        "JAVA_HOME": "/usr/lib/jvm/java-21-openjdk",
        "MAVEN_OPTS": "-Dmaven.repo.local=/root/.m2/repository"
      },
      "packages": [
        "openjdk-21",
        "maven-3.9",
        "ca-certificates"
      ]
    },
    "metadata": {
      "build_system": "Maven",
      "framework": "Spring Boot",
      "language": "Java",
      "project_name": "example-app",
      "reasoning": "Detected from pom.xml in "
    },
    "runtime": {
      "command": [
        "java",
        "-jar",
        "/app/example-app-1.0.0.jar"
      ],
      "copy": [
        {
          "from": "target/example-app-1.0.0.jar",
          "to": "/app/example-app-1.0.0.jar"
        },
        {
          "from": "target/lib/",
          "to": "/app/lib"
        }
      ],
      "env": {
        "CLASSPATH": "/app/*:/app/lib/*",
        "JAVA_HOME": "/usr/lib/jvm/java-21-openjdk",
        "PATH": "/usr/lib/jvm/java-21-openjdk/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin"
      },
      "health": {
        "endpoint": "/health"
      },
      "packages": [
        "openjdk-21-jre"
      ],
      "ports": [
        8080
      ],
      "workdir": "/app"
    },
    "version": "1.0"
  }
]


Return JSON ONLY with build configuration using Wolfi package names:
{
  "name": "zig",
  "manifest_files": ["build.zig"],
  "build_commands": ["zig build -Doptimize=ReleaseSafe"],
  "cache_dirs": ["zig-cache", ".zig-cache"],
  "build_packages": ["zig"],
  "runtime_packages": ["glibc", "ca-certificates"],
  "artifacts": ["zig-out/bin/hello"],
  "common_ports": [],
  "confidence": 0.9
}

Wolfi package name guidance:
- Always specify version-specific packages (e.g., nodejs-22, not nodejs)
- For Node.js, use packages like: nodejs-22, nodejs-20, nodejs-18
- For Python, use packages like: python-3.12, python-3.11, python-3.10
- For Java, use packages like: openjdk-21, openjdk-17, openjdk-11
- For common packages: glibc, ca-certificates, build-base, gcc, openssl-dev, pkgconf
- Leave packages empty if you're unsure - the build system will validate
